[3] Costa Rica
Date: Tue 24 May 2005
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: Teletica, Costa Rica, 24 May 2005 [translated by Mod.JG, edited]
<http://www.teletica.com/archivo/tn7/nac/2005/05/24/mosquito.htm>

During the rainy season, there is a higher frequency of _Aedes aegypti_ bites
-----------------------------------------------
The 1st case of dengue hemorrhagic fever has been reported in Orotina. It
is a 28-year-old woman who was referred to Monser Sanabria Hospital in
Puntarenas. Dengue fever is becoming more prevalent. For the same time
period in 2004, 2679 cases of dengue fever were reported, and we already
have 3560 cases for 2005.
Summer time was the ideal time to eliminate mosquito breeding places, and
we have to act rapidly these days, since _Aedes aegypti_ may be closer than
we imagine.
Last year, 11 cases of dengue hemorrhagic fever occurred, and no deaths
were reported. Limon and Pacifico Central areas are the favorite breeding
places for the mosquitoes.
--
