[4] Guatemala
Date: Tue 24 May 2005
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: Mi Punto.com Noticias, Venezuela, 24 May 2005 [translated by
Mod.JG, edited]
<http://www.mipunto.com/punto_noticias/noticia_medicina.jsp?>

A campaign is announced for dengue fever prevention in Guatemala because of
the upcoming rainy season
-----------------------------------------------
Official sources said last Tuesday [17 May 2005] that Guatemala's
Government will start next Thursday a nationally-based campaign for dengue
fever (both classic and hemorrhagic forms) prevention. This disease usually
strikes the country during the rainy season, and it caused 9 deaths last year.
The campaign will involve the delivery of information regarding dengue, as
well as fumigation and rubbish and water recipient elimination, since the
latter serve as breeding places for the mosquito that acts as a vector for
dengue fever, said Dr. Mario Gudiel, Director of the Health Care Integrated
System.
The officer explained that during 2005, 1106 dengue fever cases, and only 3
cases of dengue hemorrhagic fever, were reported throughout the country,
but there have been no deaths.
Meanwhile, during 2004, 6000 dengue fever cases, and 30 cases of dengue
hemorrhagic fever, were reported, and there were 9 deaths.
According to the Meteorology Institute, winter season has already started
in Guatemala, and it will last for 5 months.
--
