[5] Ecuador
Date: Wed 25 May 2005
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: Radio Sucre, Ecuador, 24 May 2005 [translated by Mod.JG, edited]
<http://www.radiosucre.com.ec/detalle.php?id=23227&idsec=1>

There is an increase in the number of patients with dengue fever
-----------------------------------------------
Most people affected by the disease are children. That is why the City
Council schedules community activities, as well as fumigation and the
delivery of educational material regarding dengue, malaria, leptospirosis, etc.
This campaign will be carried out in high risk areas and in some other
provinces.
